## (3)(a) 6G Standardization Process

> Discuss the standardisation process for getting 6G into the market. *(6 marks)*

> *Learn more: [6G Standardization](/wireless-communications/5g/6g-standardization)*

---

Every cellular generation follows a **three-phase process**:

| Phase | Duration | What Happens |
|-------|----------|--------------|
| **Vision & Requirements** | Years 1-3 | ITU-R defines targets |
| **Technology Development** | Years 3-7 | 3GPP writes specifications |
| **Deployment** | Years 7-10+ | Networks go live |

---

**Phase 1: ITU-R sets the vision**

ITU-R defines **IMT-2030** (the 6G requirements), specifying targets for speed, latency, and new capabilities.

**Phase 2: 3GPP writes the specs**

3GPP creates the actual technical specifications in **Releases** (Release 21-22 expected for 6G).

**Phase 3: Deployment**

Operators build networks, manufacturers create devices.

---

**6G Timeline:**

| Year | Milestone |
|------|-----------|
| 2023 | ITU-R starts IMT-2030 framework |
| 2027 | Requirements finalized |
| 2030 | First 6G specifications |
| 2030-2035 | Commercial deployment |

