## (3)(b) 5G Deployment Options

> Describe the 5G deployment options. *(4 marks)*

> *Learn more: [5G Deployment Options](/wireless-communications/5g/deployment-options)*

---

**Two main approaches:**

| Option | Name | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| **NSA** | Non-Standalone | 5G radio + **4G core** |
| **SA** | Standalone | 5G radio + **5G core** |

---

**NSA (Option 3):**
- Uses existing 4G infrastructure
- 5G provides fast data, 4G handles control
- Faster and cheaper to deploy
- *Limited 5G features*

**SA (Option 2):**
- Completely new 5G network
- Full 5G capabilities (network slicing, ultra-low latency)
- More expensive, takes longer
- *The end goal*

> **Migration path:** Option 1 (4G) → Option 3 (NSA) → Option 2 (SA)

